"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484452","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-04-11","<p>The management of energy companies’ retail operations, including the location of its staff, is a commercial matter for the individual companies.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-04-11T11:25:11.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484452/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484452/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-03-22","Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will make it a condition of energy firms' licences that the staff of those firms' entire retail operation are directly employed in the UK.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","32181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484453","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-31","<p>By convention, the Secretary of State for Justice only recommends the exercise of the Royal Prerogative of Mercy to grant a free pardon where evidence has come to light which demonstrates conclusively that the convicted individual was innocent and where all of the relevant appeal mechanisms have been exhausted.</p><p> </p><p>As far as I am aware, no approach has been made either to the Court of Appeal or to the Criminal Cases Review Commission to appeal or review the conviction of Dic Penderyn. In light of that, it would not be appropriate for the Secretary of State for Justice to consider whether to recommend to Her Majesty The Queen that she exercise the Royal Prerogative of Mercy.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2016-03-31T11:31:57.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484453/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484453/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-22","Dic Penderyn","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will conduct a new review of the case for recommending a pardon for Dic Penderyn.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","32201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484454","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-30","<p>We regularly discuss human rights concerns with the UN Office for the High Commissioner on Human Rights. On 3 March 2016, Baroness Anelay spoke to the High Commissioner in advance of the 31st session of the Human Rights Council.</p><p>The UK continues to encourage and support the Government of Bahrain in ensuring full implementation of the Bahrain Independent Commission of Inquiry recommendations, as well as those accepted in their UN Universal Periodic Review. We are offering UK assistance to help them achieve this and believe our approach is the most constructive way to achieve long-lasting and sustainable reform in Bahrain.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-03-30T12:28:20.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484454/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484454/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-22","Bahrain: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has received from the UN High Commissioner on human rights and political prisoners in Bahrain and on the implications for UK policy on Bahrain of the human rights situation in that country.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","32202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484455","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-04-01","<p>We are carefully considering the judgment and will make a further announcement in due course.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-04-01T12:04:33.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484455/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484455/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-22","Legal Aid Scheme: Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the Court of Appeal's recent decision on domestic violence evidential requirements for legal aid, what interim steps his Department plans to make for victims of domestic violence whose evidence is more than 24 months old.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","32203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484456","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-30","<p>The UK encourages Bahrain to respect the rights of all peaceful opposition figures. We call on the Bahraini government to act proportionately in all such cases to protect the universal rights of freedom of expression and assembly. We also continue to encourage the Government of Bahrain to meets its human rights obligations and honour all conventions to which it is a party – including on citizenship rights. We regularly discuss human rights with the Government of Bahrain. I most recently raised human rights with the Bahraini Ambassador to the UK, His Excellency Sheikh Fawaz bin Mohammed Al Khalifa, on 8 March.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-03-30T12:26:54.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484456/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484456/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-22","Bahrain: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the government of Bahrain pressing for (a) the release of all people arrested in relation to peaceful protest and (b) reconsideration of the July 2014 amendments to the nationality laws in that country.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","32204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484457","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-30","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office issued a statement on 16 March condemning the Government of Israel's decision to expand settlements in the West Bank.</p><p>On 18 February, during my visit to Israel, I discussed the issue of settlements with Israeli Prime Minister, Benjamin Netanyahu, reiterating the UK's position. Our Embassy regularly raises this issue with the Israeli authorities, making clear the UK’s firm and consistent opposition to illegal construction of settlements.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-03-30T12:23:46.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484457/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484457/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/484457/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-03-22","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his Israeli counterpart on settlement activity in the West Bank.","true","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","32092"
